{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_28","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry:2.0.0-RC2`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-8420-library-new-request-org.springframework.ai-spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry-2.0.0-RC2-e5954ff5\n\nThe most likely failing stage was generated test validation. The first Gradle run failed in JVM tests because `autoConfigurationBacksOffWhenApplicationProvidesRetryBeans()` expected a single `RetryTemplate`, but both `retryTemplate` and `customRetryTemplate` were present (`NoUniqueBeanDefinitionException` in `logs/org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry:2.0.0-RC2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-27T02-46-19-310256Z.log`). After the test was revised, repeated `nativeTest` runs still failed because the generated setup was missing Spring Boot test support; all native tests errored with `ClassNotFoundException: org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SharedMetadataReaderFactoryContextInitializer` (`logs/org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry:2.0.0-RC2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-27T02-50-56-208090Z.log`, with the same pattern in `logs/org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry:2.0.0-RC2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-27T02-48-09-878574Z.log` and `logs/org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry:2.0.0-RC2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-27T02-50-28-874488Z.log`). The generation log also shows the model reported that it “did not run/compile tests,” and the run metrics still ended with `status: failure`, `iterations: 4`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file/metadata_file: None` (`logs/org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry:2.0.0-RC2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-27T02-50-28-846329Z.log`, `stats/org.springframework.ai/spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry/2.0.0-RC2/execution-metrics.json`).\n\nA later human-intervention repair appears to have fixed this by adding `spring-boot-test` and switching to `ApplicationContextRunner`; the follow-up runs passed in `logs/org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry:2.0.0-RC2/metadata-fix/codex.log` and `logs/org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry:2.0.0-RC2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-27T03-10-21-985996Z.log`.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch against the later passing repair, especially the test setup and dependencies.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.springframework.ai:spring-ai-autoconfigure-retry:2.0.0-RC2` after ensuring Spring Boot test support is present.\n3. If the run is green, refresh the metrics/output artifacts and open a manual PR from the preserved branch."}}
